'''Haseeb Ahmed Drabu''' (born c. 1961) was the Chairman and Chief Executive of the [[Jammu & Kashmir Bank]] from 2005 to 2010.<ref name=r1/> 

Drabu was born and educated in India, receiving a M & D. Phil (Doctorate) in Economics from [[Jawaharlal Nehru University]], [[Delhi]]. He was a National Editor of the ''[[Business Standard]]'', where he set up a research bureau in the newspaper and he served as a Consultant to the [[Asian Development Bank]].<ref name=r1/>

Drabu started his career with the Government of India in 1990, first with the perspective Planning Division of the [[Planning Commission (India)|Planning Commission of India]], then as a consultant to the Economic Advisory Council of the Prime Minister and finally with the Tenth Finance Commission.<ref name=r1/>

Drabu was an economic advisor (with a Minister of State Status) to the Government of [[Jammu and Kashmir]] between January 2003 to 2009 and has formulated the state's first ever zero deficit budget and planned wide ranging tax reforms, methods of expenditure compression and an innovative scheme to reduce the debt stock of the State Government.<ref name=r1>[http://investing.businessweek.com/research/stocks/people/person.asp?personId=24561261&ticker=13421491&previousCapId=13421491&previousTitle=Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20Bank%20Ltd Haseeb Ahmed Drabu M & D.Phil Economics]. Bloomberg Business</ref>

He joined [[PDP]] and contested assembly election in 2014 and won.<ref>http://www.hindustantimes.com/punjab/jandk/ex-j-amp-k-bank-chairman-drabu-joins-pdp-will-be-srinagar-face/article1-1235941.aspx</ref> <ref>http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/pdp-mehbooba-mufti-nc-national-conference-congress-jammu-and-kashmir-government-formation-n-n-vohra/1/410470.html</ref>

